{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QvfZSoqBEG52dBB7pMsa9V","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ETL pipeline completed successfully. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root Cause Identified:**\n- The job had `--driver-memory 256m` and `spark.executor.memory=256m`, but Spark requires at least ~471MB of system memory to initialize. The error was:\n  ```\n  System memory 259522560 must be at least 471859200\n  ```\n- Additionally, user_id=999 holds ~50% of records with a 500x skew ratio, making the Stage 3 `GROUP BY user_id` aggregation especially memory-intensive.\n\n**Fix Applied (`etl-job.yaml`):**\n1. Raised `--driver-memory` from `256m` → `1g`\n2. Raised `spark.executor.memory` from `256m` → `1g`\n3. Added `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true` and `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true` to handle the data skew at partition level\n4. Scaled `spark-worker` deployment from 1 → 4 replicas with `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=2G`\n\n**Result:** Job status is `Complete 1/1` and the log ends with `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2417,"cache_read_input_tokens":35826,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2417},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abfc724c-8222-4ae1-8eaf-df813a524932","uuid":"799c4dfe-6072-4ae2-bae8-7c90cb3bc87d","request_id":"req_011CcgUfm2Tit72uuWNqRQj8"}
